The United States and the United Kingdom have recognized that cybersecurity is a significant threat to their economic and national security. They have agreed to strengthen their cooperation in this area by enhancing the cybersecurity of critical infrastructure, increasing threat information sharing, and conducting joint cybersecurity exercises. The two countries will also establish a joint cyber cell to facilitate the sharing of cyber threat information. Additionally, they will provide funding for a new Fulbright Cyber Security Award, allowing scholars to conduct cybersecurity research. Furthermore, the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and the University of Cambridge will participate in a cybersecurity contest to promote cybersecurity research at the highest academic level.